
Features Till java 1.8

Interface will only have abstract methods -> we cannot define methods in interface , we can only declare it. All methods of interface will be public abstract.



----------------------Features of java 1.8

Function interface and lambda expressions
forEach method in iterable interface
Optional class
Default and static methods in interface
Method references
Java Stream api for Bulk Data operations on CORE_JAVA.DataStructure.Collections
Java Date time api
Base64 Encode/Decode
Collection Api improvements
Java IO improvements

-----
Functional interface (Single abstract method interface)
   A functional interface allow only one "Abstract method" as its member.
   @FunctionalInterface
   public interface functionalInterface(){
    public void onlyOneMethod();
   }
   you can omit the annotation , it is there to just tell the compiler that interface will have one abstract method.

-------
Optional Class
                Optional class is a public Final class and it is used to deal with null pointer exceptions
                String[] str = new String[10];
                Optional<String>checkNull =  Optional.ofNullable(str[5]);



Collection Api improvements
            Map collection has replaceAll(), computer(), merge() methods added.
            key collision improved in hashmap.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------Java-11

Commercial use of Java-11 new features require a license.

Type interface for lambda expressions
         You can choose to specify types of lambda parameters or omitting them when writing a lambda expression.
